HEADWORD: Nauplius
<hw>Nau"pli*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Nauplii</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a kind of shellfish,
fr. Gr. <grk>nay^s</grk> ship + <?/ to sail.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A crustacean larva having three pairs of locomotive organs
(corresponding to the antennules, antennae, and mandibles), a median
eye, and little or no segmentation of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

